Section --- Managing Services

  We will see the usage of sc, the Windows Command Line Service controler utility.

  As an attacker we need to:

  - Determine what services are running
  - Attempt to disable antivirus
  - Modify existing services on a system


-- SERVICE CONTROLLER --

Query, modify and manage host services locally and over the network.

> sc --> Description of the command "SC is a command line program used for communicating with the Service Control Manager and services."


-- QUERY SERVICES --

Get information such as the process state, process id (pid), and service type.

